# L.L.O.Y.D. ‚Äî Language Layers Over Your Data

A symbolic drift detection and tone deviation engine that listens like a human would ‚Äî tracking not just sentiment, but **meaning breaks**, **symbolic conflict**, and **emotional escalation**.

---

## üîç What Is LLOYD?

LLOYD isn‚Äôt another sentiment classifier.  
It‚Äôs a drift-aware analyzer that tells you when **a conversation turns** ‚Äî emotionally, symbolically, or relationally.

From sarcastic reversals to performative breakdowns, LLOYD is designed to detect subtle shifts in tone that traditional NLP often misses.

> ‚úÖ *Calibration is limited, but customizable.*  
> LLOYD is lightly tuned, but designed for adaptation to domain-specific tone models.

> ‚úÖ *Work-in-progress with feedback welcome.*  
> This is an active project ‚Äî contributions, questions, and use-case tests are encouraged.  
> Contact: [putmanmodel@pm.me](mailto:putmanmodel@pm.me)

---

## ‚ú® What Makes It Different?

## üß± How LLOYD Compares: Above the Stack

LLOYD doesn‚Äôt just label tone ‚Äî it listens like a person, tracking symbolic shifts, emotional slope, and layered meaning.

Here‚Äôs how it stacks up:

| Tier            | Model Type            | Capabilities                                  | Notes                                                  |
|-----------------|-----------------------|-----------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| üü© **LLOYD**     | Symbolic Drift Engine | Emotional drift scoring, override logic, symbolic pattern detection, sarcasm flags, badges | ‚úÖ Built for human-level nuance and meaning tracking   |
| üü® Mid-Level     | Sentiment Classifier  | Polarity scoring, intensity detection         | ‚ö†Ô∏è Misses sarcasm, symbolic shifts, escalation cues     |
| üü• Legacy        | Keyword Matcher       | Token triggers, emotion word lists            | ‚ùå Fails on nuance, symbolic inversion, or context      |

> üü¢ *LLOYD hears the difference between ‚ÄúGreat job‚Äù and ‚ÄúGreat job‚Ä¶‚Äù*  
> üî¥ *Others just check for ‚Äúpositive‚Äù or ‚Äúnegative.‚Äù*

> **Please note**: LLOYD is already scaffolded for *Drift Memory* and short-term tone weighting ‚Äî  
> this table excludes those in-progress features until the official demo drops.

‚ú® *It‚Äôs better ‚Äî and it‚Äôs not even done yet.*

- Symbolic override detection (`"Great job‚Ä¶"`, `"You helped?"`)
- Emphasis escalation tracking (`ALL CAPS`, `!!!`, emoji floods)
- Drift memory modeling to detect emotional pressure buildup
- Mirror match and mocked echo detection
- Output includes rationale, badge label, override label

---

## üß™ Quick Start

```bash
pip install lloyd-engine  # placeholder for future release
python devtools/run.py
```

Sample output:

```text
Badge    : üõ≥ override: emphasis_override
üîπ [sarcasm_hint]
Baseline : Great job.
Incoming : Great job...
Drift    : True
Label    : sarcasm_hint
Œî        : 80
Rationale: Trailing or embedded sarcasm marker detected.
```

---

## üåê Streamlit GUI

Launch the visual interface:
```bash
streamlit run devtools/sandbox_demo/app/app.py
```

Try this real example:

```text
Baseline : Why wasn‚Äôt this done earlier?
Incoming : You are garbage.
Drift    : True
Label    : hostile_emphasis
Œî        : 92
Badge    : üõ≥ override: hostile_emphasis
Rationale: Intensified hostile language detected ‚Äî override triggered.
```

